        <abstract>
            <p>Relationship of schists to alternating beds of slate in western Tierra del Fuego and the Chonos Islands.</p>
            <p>Comments on Sharpe’s theory of curved cleavage planes.</p>
            <p>Example of metamorphosis in a "clay-slate porphyry region". Importance of previous lines of cleavage and stratification in foliation of metamorphosed rock.</p>
        </abstract>
